<p class=""><h2>Key Challenges in the Display Case Lighting Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Energy Efficiency Regulations:</strong> Stricter regulations aimed at reducing energy consumption pose a challenge for manufacturers to develop lighting solutions that comply without sacrificing performance.</li>    <li><strong>Technological Obsolescence:</strong> Rapid advancements in LED technology can make existing lighting solutions obsolete, necessitating continuous investment in research and development.</li>    <li><strong>Design Flexibility:</strong> Display cases often require unique lighting solutions tailored to specific products. This necessitates high levels of customization, which can drive up costs and lead times.</li>    <li><strong>Cost of Raw Materials:</strong> Fluctuations in the prices of raw materials, including semiconductors and glass, can impact production costs and profitability.</li>    <li><strong>Competitive Pricing Pressure:</strong> Increased competition within the market compels manufacturers to lower prices, which can squeeze margins and affect overall financial health.</li>    <li><strong>Environmental Concerns:</strong> Growing consumer awareness about environmental sustainability challenges manufacturers to adopt eco-friendly materials and production processes.</li></ul><h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Display Case Lighting Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>LED Technology Innovations:</strong> Continuous improvements in LED efficiency, color rendering, and lifetime present an opportunity for manufacturers to offer superior products that meet diverse consumer needs.</li>    <li><strong>Smart Lighting Solutions:</strong> The integration of IoT technology into display case lighting represents a growing market. Smart lighting can enhance energy management and offer customizable lighting experiences, appealing to modern retail and display environments.</li>    <li><strong>Focus on Aesthetics:</strong> As retailers place greater emphasis on 